TITLE: Implementing Live Product Search Component in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a live product search component using Symfony UX Live Components. It includes LiveProps and a method to fetch products based on the search query.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/ux/blob/2.x/src/LiveComponent/doc/index.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
// src/Twig/Components/ProductSearch.php
namespace App\Twig\Components;

use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Attribute\AsLiveComponent;
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Attribute\LiveProp;
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\DefaultActionTrait;

#[AsLiveComponent]
class ProductSearch
{
    use DefaultActionTrait;

    #[LiveProp(writable: true)]
    public string $query = '';

    public function __construct(private ProductRepository $productRepository)
    {
    }

    public function getProducts(): array
    {
        // example method that returns an array of Products
        return $this->productRepository->search($this->query);
    }
}
```

