TITLE: Dynamic URL Parameter Name Modification with Modifiers
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use a modifier function to dynamically change URL parameter names, which is useful when using the same component multiple times on a page to avoid parameter name collisions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/ux/blob/2.x/src/LiveComponent/doc/index.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_108

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
// ...
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Metadata\UrlMapping;

#[AsLiveComponent]
class SearchModule
{
    #[LiveProp(writable: true, url: true, modifier: 'modifyQueryProp')]
    public string $query = '';

    #[LiveProp]
    public ?string $alias = null;

    public function modifyQueryProp(LiveProp $liveProp): LiveProp
    {
        if ($this->alias) {
            $liveProp = $liveProp->withUrl(new UrlMapping(as: $this->alias));
        }
        return $liveProp;
    }
}
```

