TITLE: Updating PHP Class for Live Component Definition
DESCRIPTION: Shows the transition from implementing LiveComponentInterface to using PHP 8 attributes for defining a Live Component, including changes in property and method annotations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/ux/blob/2.x/src/LiveComponent/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-14_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use App\Entity\Notification;
use App\Repository\NotificationRepository;
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Attribute\LiveAction;
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\Attribute\LiveProp;
use Symfony\UX\LiveComponent\LiveComponentInterface;

final class NotificationComponent implements LiveComponentInterface
{
    private NotificationRepository $repo;

    /** @LiveProp */
    public bool $expanded = false;

    public function __construct(NotificationRepository $repo)
    {
        $this->repo = $repo;
    }

    /** @LiveAction */
    public function toggle(): void
    {
        $this->expanded = !$this->expanded;
    }

    public function getNotifications(): array
    {
        return $this->repo->findAll();
    }

    public static function getComponentName(): string
    {
        return 'notification';
    }
}
```

