TITLE: Creating Broadcast Template in Twig
DESCRIPTION: This Twig template defines how entity updates are broadcast using Turbo Streams. It includes blocks for create, update, and remove actions that will be automatically used by Symfony UX Turbo.
SOURCE: https://github.com/symfony/ux/blob/2.x/src/Turbo/doc/index.rst#2025-04-14_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: html+twig
CODE:
```
{# templates/broadcast/Book.stream.html.twig #}
{% block create %}
    <turbo-stream action="append" targets="#books">
        <template>
            <div id="{{ 'book_' ~ id }}">{{ entity.title }} (#{{ id }})</div>
        </template>
    </turbo-stream>
{% endblock %}

{% block update %}
    <turbo-stream action="update" targets="#book_{{ id }}">
        <template>
            {{ entity.title }} (#{{ id }}, updated)
        </template>
    </turbo-stream>
{% endblock %}

{% block remove %}
    <turbo-stream action="remove" targets="#book_{{ id }}"></turbo-stream>
{% endblock %}
```

